{
  "stem": "12289.3",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So now and then, we managed to get people back, if he could prove that they had Swedish passports and all that.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, that-- that was Wallenberg's way of doing it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He-- he had the-- spoke to the commandant.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he gave him a-- a bottle of cognac or whatever, and so on, and got on speaking terms with him, and so on, and-- and said that, here are some people here with Swedish passports.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And-- and how he-- how he negotiated that?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He was very clever man in that way.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it's, of course, a question how many we saved that way.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I would guess-- also, the Swiss, the Swiss embassy and all that followed our example.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I think we-- we managed, together with the Swiss, to save a couple of thousand people that way.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we had-- and that is where I was involved, because it was with the Foreign Office.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that-- I felt free then to negotiate with them.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that is how this critical situation that came about when the-- the-- the Nyilas-- that's the Hungarian name of the Hungarian Nazis-- when they, all of a sudden, after the 15th of October then, when they took over, decided that these protective passports had-- had no value any longer.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that was, of course, a catastrophical situation for us.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that is how Wallenberg managed to, through the wife of the then foreign minister-- Kemeny was his name-- she approached.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "She was suffering very much of-- of seeing all this, because she was a-- a rather-- she was a very-- she was a humanitarian person.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And she'd always objected against this-- these kind of methods and all that.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "She approached Wallenberg and said, what can I do to help?",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
